      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know what you're saying, but it's different when you're actually the one living it. every time they have to come over just to help me with the groceries or the meds, i can see it in their eyes... they're just exhausted. i feel like a weight around their necks. it doesn't feel like i'm 'balancing' anything, it just feels like i'm draining them dry.",
